divs: Sighting DetailsI was making coffee in my kitchen, looking out the window that faces south, and saw a very shiny cigar-shaped object traveling south to north-west. I thought it was a jet at first, based upon how fast it was going, but I realized there were no wings and no sound associated with a normal aircraft. I went outside to take a better look at it, but as far as I could tell this was not a conventional aircraft. It had a cigar shape to it and had a wierd "back end", similar to a submarine with a propeller. It was traveling in a relatively straight line, no variations to speed or direction. I watched it until it disappeared from my view over the roof of the house next door. It was a very strange experience. I didn't feel scared, just puzzled. I'd like to know if others saw this and what they thought.
